'''Carina Maria Schlebusch''' is an [[evolutionary biologist]] at the [[University of Uppsala]] in [[Sweden]]. She is a specialist in the population history of [[Africa]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://katalog.uu.se/profile/?id=N9-1616 |title=Carina Schlebusch - Uppsala University, Sweden |website=katalog.uu.se |accessdate=2 October 2017}}</ref> In 2017 she was the co-author of a paper that suggested that modern [[human|humans]] emerged more than 300,000 years ago.<ref>{{cite biorxiv |first1=Carina M. |last1=Schlebusch |first2=Helena |last2=Malmström |first3=Torsten |last3=Günther |first4=Per |last4=Sjödin |first5=Alexandra |last5=Coutinho |first6=Hanna |last6=Edlund |first7=Arielle R. |last7=Munters |first8=Maryna |last8=Steyn |first9=Himla |last9=Soodyall |first10=Marlize |last10=Lombard |first11=Mattias |last11=Jakobsson |date=5 June 2017 |title=Ancient genomes from southern Africa pushes modern human divergence beyond 260,000 years ago |biorxiv=145409}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal  |first1=Carina M. |last1=Schlebusch |first2=Helena |last2=Malmström |first3=Torsten |last3=Günther |first4=Per |last4=Sjödin |first5=Alexandra |last5=Coutinho |first6=Hanna |last6=Edlund |first7=Arielle R. |last7=Munters |first8=Mário |last8=Vicente |first9=Maryna |last9=Steyn |first10=Himla |last10=Soodyall |first11=Marlize |last11=Lombard |first12=Mattias |last12=Jakobsson |date=28 September 2017 |title=Southern African ancient genomes estimate modern human divergence to 350,000 to 260,000 years ago |journal=Science |volume=358 |issue=6363 |pages=652 |doi=10.1126/science.aao6266|pmid=28971970 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2017/09/170928142016.htm |title=Modern humans emerged more than 300,000 years ago new study suggests |website=ScienceDaily.com |accessdate=2 October 2017}}</ref>

