An '''Ellis Island Special''' is a [[family name]] that is perceived or labeled, incorrectly,<ref name=Horn>{{cite journal |last=Horn |first=Dara |date=Summer 2010 |title=The Myth of Ellis Island and Other Tales of Origin |journal=Azure |issue=41 |issn=0829-982X |accessdate=June 13, 2011 |url=http://azure.org.il/article.php?id=544}}</ref> as having been altered by immigration officials at the [[Ellis Island|Ellis Island Immigration Station]], when a family reached the United States, typically from Europe in the 19th and early 20th centuries.<ref name=Murtha>{{cite news |title=Laptop Anthropologist: Meeting my sister from another mister |first=Tara |last=Murtha |url=http://www.philadelphiaweekly.com/news-and-opinion/laptop-anthropologist/laptop_anthropologist-38470274.html?page=2 |newspaper=Philadelphia Weekly |issn= |date=August 6, 2008 |accessdate=June 10, 2011 |quote= |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5zLZkRs3C?url=http://www.philadelphiaweekly.com/news-and-opinion/laptop-anthropologist/laptop_anthropologist-38470274.html?page=2 |archivedate=June 10, 2011 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref name=Maniaty>{{cite book |last1=Maniaty |first1=Tony |title=Smyrna: a novel |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kcVHAAAAYAAJ&q=%22an+ellis+island+special%22&dq=%22an+ellis+island+special%22&hl=en&ei=oZTyTd37JsuDtgfFzoSKBw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDQQ6AEwAg |accessdate=June 10, 2011 |year=1989 |publisher=Penguin Books Australia |page=135}}</ref><ref name=Toor>{{cite web|url=http://readthebestwriting.com/?p=440 |title=Riding an Elephant |first=Rachel |last=Toor |date=April 2011 |work=Ascent |publisher=Concordia College |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110825180820/http://readthebestwriting.com/?p=440 |archivedate=August 25, 2011 |accessdate=June 10, 2011 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> In popular thought,<ref name=Christensen> {{cite book |last1=Christensen |first1=Linda |title=Reading, writing, and rising up: teaching about social justice and the power of the written word |url=http://www.google.com/search?hl=en&tbo=1&tbm=bks&q=%22shortened+at+ellis+island%22+christensen&aq=f&aqi=&aql=&oq= |accessdate=June 20, 2011 |year=2000 |publisher=Rethinking Schools |isbn=978-0-942961-25-6 |page=10}}</ref><ref name=Caracciolo>{{cite book |last1=Caracciolo |first1=Mike |last2=Benson |first2=Michael |title=Go F*** Yourself: The Kid from Brooklyn's Rants and Other Stuff |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3xBydcw4Nv4C&pg=PA124&dq=%22ellis+island+shortened%22&hl=en&ei=pYf2TdriA8PUgQftpoXICw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=6&ved=0CEYQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=%22ellis%20island%20shortened%22&f=false |year=2007 |publisher=Citadel Press |isbn=978-0-8065-2865-6 |page=124}}</ref> some family lore,<ref name=Horn /><ref name=Gertz> {{cite news |title = Around the world in 500 days |first = Kaitlin |last = Gertz |author2 = Gertz, Thomas |url = http://www.nctimes.com/travel/article_a15ef29e-21a4-5d7c-bde2-245c883a2fdf.html |newspaper = North County Times |date = October 28, 2007 |accessdate = June 10, 2011 |archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5zLbZjXAQ?url=http://www.nctimes.com/travel/article_a15ef29e-21a4-5d7c-bde2-245c883a2fdf.html |archivedate = June 10, 2011 |deadurl = yes |df = }}</ref><ref name=Cohen>{{cite book |last1=Cohen |first1=Leah Hager |title=Train go sorry: inside a deaf world |url=http://www.google.com/search?tbm=bks&q=%22ellis+island+altered%22+cohen&aq=f&aqi=&aql=&oq= |year=1994 |publisher=Houghton Mifflin |isbn=978-0-395-63625-1 |page=68}}</ref><ref name=Bell>{{cite book |last1=Bell |first1=Charles Greenleaf |title=Millennial Harvest: the life and collected poems of Charles Greenleaf Bell |url=http://www.google.com/search?q=%22altered+at+ellis+island%22&btnG=Search+Books&tbm=bks&tbo=1 |accessdate=June 10, 2011 |year=2006 |publisher=Lumen Books |isbn=978-0-930829-60-5 |page=80}}</ref> and literary fiction,<ref name=Maniaty /><ref name=Schneider>{{cite book |last1=Schneider |first1=Ilene |title=Chanukah Guilt |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CE01zd8LLOoC&pg=PA310&dq=%22ellis+island+shortened%22&hl=en&ei=pYf2TdriA8PUgQftpoXICw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CDwQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=%22ellis%20island%20shortened%22&f=false |year=2007 |publisher=Swimming Kangaroo Books |isbn=978-1-934041-31-4 |page=310}}</ref> some family names were seen as having been shortened by immigration officials for ease of pronunciation or record-keeping, or lack of understanding of the true name—even though name changes were made by the immigrants themselves at other times.<ref name=Horn /> Among the family names that are perceived as being Ellis Island Specials are some that were supposedly more identifiably Jewish, resulting in last names that were not identifiably so.<ref name=Horn /><ref name=Toor />
The phrase "Ellis Island Special" has also been adopted by some food vendors and applied to sandwiches, among other foods.<ref name=Pahigian> {{cite book |last1=Pahigian |first1=Joshua |last2=O'Connell |first2=Kevin |title=The Ultimate Baseball Road-Trip: A Fan's Guide to Major League Stadiums |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FM1YtoSZEnAC&pg=PA378&dq=%22ellis+island+special%22+sandwich&hl=en&ei=p6LyTbK7I8TAgQei8LnSCw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CDEQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22ellis%20island%20special%22%20sandwich&f=false |accessdate=June 10, 2011 |year=2004 |publisher=Globe Pequot |isbn=978-1-59228-159-6 |page=378}}</ref>
