{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}} {{Infobox television |show_name = Future Fantastic |image = |caption = |show_name_2 = |genre = [[Science fiction]] [[documentary film|documentary]] |creator = |writer = |director = Penny Southgate |developer = |presenter = [[Gillian Anderson]] |starring = |voices = |narrated = |theme_music_composer = HAL / real VIVID |opentheme = |endtheme = |composer = |country = United Kingdom |language = English |num_seasons = 1 |num_episodes = 9 |list_episodes = |executive_producer = Edward Briffa |producer = David McNab, Jasper James |editor = Allan Fowlie, David Sleight |location = |cinematography = |camera = |runtime = 24 minutes |channel = [[BBC]] |picture_format = 4:3 |audio_format = |first_run = 1996 |first_aired = |last_aired = |preceded_by = |followed_by = |related = |website = |production_website = }}
'''''Future Fantastic''''' was a British [[documentary film|documentary]] [[television series]] which premiered in 1996. This show looked at the how science and science fiction complement each other, and how ideas and technologies from the past are helping to shape our future. The series was [[narrator|narrated]] by [[Gillian Anderson]] and [[production company|co-produced]] by the [[British Broadcasting Corporation]], [[The Learning Channel]] and [[Pro Sieben]].
== Episodes ==
# ''Alien'': Discusses the possibility of encountering [[Extraterrestrial life|intelligent life]] on other planets. # ''I, Robot'': Discusses the evolving and growing role of [[artificial intelligence]], [[computer]]s, and [[robot]]s in our everyday life. # ''Starman'': Looks at how we might eventually reach the [[star]]s. # ''Incredible Shrinking Planet'': Looks at the future of [[transport]], including [[teleportation]] and [[time travel]]. # ''Brave New Body'': Looks into how [[body modification]] will shape our lives in the future. # ''Weird Science'': Shows how we have come close to [[antigravity|defying gravity]], and achieving [[invisibility]] and [[Perpetual motion|perpetual energy]]. # ''Brainstorm'': Looks at technology being put into and onto people's heads to create artificial experiences. # ''Underneath a purple sky'': Looks at the future of [[space tourism]]. # ''Immortal'': Questions whether we may ever achieve [[immortality]].
== Theme music == The theme music to ''Future Fantastic'' was by HAL <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gilliananderson.ws/transcripts/96_97/97axcess.shtml |title=About HAL and Gillian's Collaboration | accessdate=1 September 2008}}</ref> who later collaborated with Gillian Anderson on the track "Extremis" which was released by [[Virgin Records]] in 1997.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://raft.vmg.co.uk/hal/pressconf/ |title=Hal press conference |publisher=Virgin |date=13 May 1997 |accessdate=1 September 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20021027155825/http://raft.vmg.co.uk/hal/pressconf/ |archivedate=27 October 2002 }}</ref>
