{{Infobox journal | italic title = force | title = Sociological Forum | cover = | editor = [[Karen A. Cerulo]] | discipline = [[Sociology]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Sociol. Forum | publisher = [[Wiley-Blackwell]] on behalf of the [[Eastern Sociological Society]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1986-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 0.908 | impact-year = 2011 | website = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1573-7861 | link1 = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1573-7861/currentissue | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.essnet.org/ | link2-name = Eastern Sociological Society | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0884-8971 | eISSN = 1573-7861 }} '''''Sociological Forum''''' is a quarterly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by [[Wiley-Blackwell]] on behalf of the [[Eastern Sociological Society]]. It has been published since 1986. The current [[editor]] is [[Karen A. Cerulo]] ([[Rutgers University]]). The journal covers all areas of [[sociology]] and related fields, emphasizing innovative direction in sociological research.
According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2011 [[impact factor]] of 0.908, ranking it 58th out of 137 journals in the category "Sociology".<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2012 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Sociology |title=2011 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |accessdate=2012-08-10 |series=Web of Science |postscript=.}}</ref>
